            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EEzra%20and%20his%20companions%20labored%20to%20reconstruct%20the%20temple%20at%20Jerusalem.%20When%20their%20actions%20were%20brought%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20Darius%20the%20king%2C%20he%20approved%20the%20building%20project.%20Furthermore%2C%20he%20supplied%20all%20the%20necessary%20materials%20for%20construction%2C%20while%20the%20people%20provided%20the%20work.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EEzra%20worked%20to%20rebuild%20a%20physical%20temple%2C%20but%20you%20are%20working%20on%20a%20spiritual%20temple%20(1%20Corinthians%203%3A10).%20God%20Himself%20has%20provided%20the%20foundation%2C%20the%20equipment%2C%20and%20the%20materials%20in%20His%20Son%2C%20Jesus%20Christ.%20You%20are%20God's%20fellow%20worker%2C%20laboring%20to%20build%20on%20this%20foundation%20the%20types%20of%20works%20that%20will%20stand%20the%20test%20of%20time%20and%20eternity.%20%22If%20the%20work%20survives%20the%20fire%2C%20that%20builder%20will%20receive%20a%20reward.%20But%20if%20the%20work%20is%20burned%20up%2C%20the%20builder%20will%20suffer%20great%20loss.%20The%20builders%20themselves%20will%20be%20saved%2C%20but%20like%20someone%20escaping%20through%20a%20wall%20of%20flames%22%20(vv.%2014-15).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYour%20work%20for%20God%20will%20become%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20you%20the%20moment%20you%20stand%20before%20the%20judgment%20seat%20of%20Christ.%20If%20your%20work%20on%20earth%20was%20hasty%2C%20superficial%2C%20and%20self-exalting%2C%20it%20will%20be%20destroyed.%20If%20it%20was%20deep%2C%20rooted%20in%20love%2C%20and%20glorifying%20only%20Christ%2C%20it%20will%20last.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThis%20spiritual%20temple%20you%20are%20building%20is%20all%20that%20is%20worthy%20of%20your%20life's%20work%2C%20so%20give%20it%20your%20all.%20You%20will%20enjoy%20the%20rewards%20of%20your%20work%20for%20eternity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Ezra.4:24-6:22",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EEzra%204%3A24-6%3A22%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_24%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Rebuilding%20Resumes%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20work%20on%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20in%20Jerusalem%20had%20stopped%2C%20and%20it%20remained%20at%20a%20standstill%20until%20the%20second%20year%20of%20the%20reign%20of%20King%20Darius%20of%20Persia.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A24%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20second%20year%20of%20Darius%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20was%20520%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20narrative%20started%20in%204%3A1-5%20is%20resumed%20at%20verse%26%23xA0%3B24.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_1%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EEzra%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20that%20time%20the%20prophets%20Haggai%20and%20Zechariah%20son%20of%20Iddo%20prophesied%20to%20the%20Jews%20in%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem.%20They%20prophesied%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%20who%20was%20over%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_2%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EZerubbabel%20son%20of%20Shealtiel%20and%20Jeshua%20son%20of%20Jehozadak%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Aramaic%20%3Cem%3EJozadak%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehozadak.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20responded%20by%20starting%20again%20to%20rebuild%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20in%20Jerusalem.%20And%20the%20prophets%20of%20God%20were%20with%20them%20and%20helped%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_3%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Tattenai%2C%20governor%20of%20the%20province%20west%20of%20the%20Euphrates%20River%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Aramaic%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20province%20beyond%20the%20river%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%205%3A6.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20Shethar-bozenai%20and%20their%20colleagues%20soon%20arrived%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWho%20gave%20you%20permission%20to%20rebuild%20this%20Temple%20and%20restore%20this%20structure%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_4%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20asked%20for%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20one%20Hebrew%20manuscript%20and%20Greek%20and%20Syriac%20versions%3B%20Masoretic%20Text%20reads%20%3Cem%3EThen%20we%20told%20them.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20names%20of%20all%20the%20men%20working%20on%20the%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_5%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20because%20their%20God%20was%20watching%20over%20them%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20Jews%20were%20not%20prevented%20from%20building%20until%20a%20report%20was%20sent%20to%20Darius%20and%20he%20returned%20his%20decision.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_6%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ETattenai%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Letter%20to%20King%20Darius%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20letter%20that%20Tattenai%20the%20governor%2C%20Shethar-bozenai%2C%20and%20the%20other%20officials%20of%20the%20province%20west%20of%20the%20Euphrates%20River%20sent%20to%20King%20Darius%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_7%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BTo%20King%20Darius.%20Greetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_8%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20king%20should%20know%20that%20we%20went%20to%20the%20construction%20site%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20great%20God%20in%20the%20province%20of%20Judah.%20It%20is%20being%20rebuilt%20with%20specially%20prepared%20stones%2C%20and%20timber%20is%20being%20laid%20in%20its%20walls.%20The%20work%20is%20going%20forward%20with%20great%20energy%20and%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_9%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWe%20asked%20the%20leaders%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWho%20gave%20you%20permission%20to%20rebuild%20this%20Temple%20and%20restore%20this%20structure%3F%26%23x2019%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_10%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20we%20demanded%20their%20names%20so%20that%20we%20could%20tell%20you%20who%20the%20leaders%20were.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_11%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20was%20their%20answer%3A%20%26%23x2018%3BWe%20are%20the%20servants%20of%20the%20God%20of%20heaven%20and%20earth%2C%20and%20we%20are%20rebuilding%20the%20Temple%20that%20was%20built%20here%20many%20years%20ago%20by%20a%20great%20king%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_12%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20because%20our%20ancestors%20angered%20the%20God%20of%20heaven%2C%20he%20abandoned%20them%20to%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20of%20Babylon%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Aramaic%20%3Cem%3ENebuchadnezzar%20the%20Chaldean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20who%20destroyed%20this%20Temple%20and%20exiled%20the%20people%20to%20Babylonia.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_13%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20King%20Cyrus%20of%20Babylon%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20King%20Cyrus%20of%20Persia%20is%20here%20identified%20as%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20because%20Persia%20had%20conquered%20the%20Babylonian%20Empire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20during%20the%20first%20year%20of%20his%20reign%2C%20issued%20a%20decree%20that%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20should%20be%20rebuilt.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_14%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Cyrus%20returned%20the%20gold%20and%20silver%20cups%20that%20Nebuchadnezzar%20had%20taken%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20had%20placed%20in%20the%20temple%20of%20Babylon.%20These%20cups%20were%20taken%20from%20that%20temple%20and%20presented%20to%20a%20man%20named%20Sheshbazzar%2C%20whom%20King%20Cyrus%20appointed%20as%20governor%20of%20Judah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_15%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20instructed%20him%20to%20return%20the%20cups%20to%20their%20place%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20to%20rebuild%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20there%20on%20its%20original%20site.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_16%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20this%20Sheshbazzar%20came%20and%20laid%20the%20foundations%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20in%20Jerusalem.%20The%20people%20have%20been%20working%20on%20it%20ever%20since%2C%20though%20it%20is%20not%20yet%20completed.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_5_17%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BTherefore%2C%20if%20it%20pleases%20the%20king%2C%20we%20request%20that%20a%20search%20be%20made%20in%20the%20royal%20archives%20of%20Babylon%20to%20discover%20whether%20King%20Cyrus%20ever%20issued%20a%20decree%20to%20rebuild%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20in%20Jerusalem.%20And%20then%20let%20the%20king%20send%20us%20his%20decision%20in%20this%20matter.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_6_1%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EEzra%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDarius%20Approves%20the%20Rebuilding%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20King%20Darius%20issued%20orders%20that%20a%20search%20be%20made%20in%20the%20Babylonian%20archives%2C%20which%20were%20stored%20in%20the%20treasury.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_6_2%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20it%20was%20at%20the%20fortress%20at%20Ecbatana%20in%20the%20province%20of%20Media%20that%20a%20scroll%20was%20found.%20This%20is%20what%20it%20said%3A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BMemorandum%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_6_3%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIn%20the%20first%20year%20of%20King%20Cyrus%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20a%20decree%20was%20sent%20out%20concerning%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20at%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BLet%20the%20Temple%20be%20rebuilt%20on%20the%20site%20where%20Jews%20used%20to%20offer%20their%20sacrifices%2C%20using%20the%20original%20foundations.%20Its%20height%20will%20be%20ninety%20feet%2C%20and%20its%20width%20will%20be%20ninety%20feet.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Aramaic%20%3Cem%3EIts%20height%20will%20be%2060%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B27.6%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%2C%20%3Cem%3Eand%20its%20width%20will%20be%2060%26%23xA0%3Bcubits.%3C%2Fem%3E%20It%20is%20commonly%20held%20that%20this%20verse%20should%20be%20emended%20to%20read%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BIts%20height%20will%20be%2030%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%20%5B45%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20or%2013.8%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%2C%20its%20length%20will%20be%2060%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%20%5B90%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20or%2027.6%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%2C%20and%20its%20width%20will%20be%2020%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%20%5B30%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20or%209.2%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%26%23x201D%3B%3B%20compare%201%26%23xA0%3BKgs%206%3A2.%20The%20emendation%20regarding%20the%20width%20is%20supported%20by%20the%20Syriac